📑 Pattern 5: Grouping Pattern
You are given a list of messy data (strings, arrays) and asked to group them by a shared characteristic.

The Concept: You must find a way to create a "Signature" or "Standardized Key" for the data. For anagrams, the signature is the sorted version of the string. The map stores <Signature, List of Original Words>.

Java Blueprint:

Java
Map<String, List<String>> groupMap = new HashMap<>();

for (String s : strs) {
    // 1. Create the standardized signature (e.g., sort the string)
    char[] chars = s.toCharArray();
    Arrays.sort(chars);
    String signature = new String(chars);
    
    // 2. Add to the group. computeIfAbsent creates the list if it doesn't exist yet!
    groupMap.computeIfAbsent(signature, k -> new ArrayList<>()).add(s);
}

// Return the grouped values as a List of Lists
return new ArrayList<>(groupMap.values());
